thread.title: Aust 'foreign affairs on the cheap'
thread.title_full: Aust 'foreign affairs on the cheap' | Business Spectator

author: AAP
title: Aust 'foreign affairs on the cheap'
text:
Australia does foreign affairs "on the cheap", according to departing ambassador to the US Kim Beazley.
The former Labor leader, whose six-year tenure is drawing to a close, says resources in Washington have been pared back over the years despite closer ties between the two nations.
"It's not good. I would think we would be well served by a more extensive department," he told The Australian .
Mr Beazley is on Monday expected to be named the next president of the Australian Institute of International Affairs upon his return to Australia.
